Module 2 - Topic 8: Simple Game Architecture
https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=IhmAr2N1o0I
Which of the following is correct in relation to game architecture?
Your answer: Breaking the game into separate components makes it easier to develop and understand the code.
The goal of good game architecture should be to create code that is easy to develop, does the job required, and is flexible enough to support changes without massive restructuring. Breaking it into separate components makes this easier.

